step.tex:
\begin{align}

\dfrac{1}{\sin  x\cos^3 x} &= 
\dfrac{\sin^2 x + \cos^2 x}{\sin x \cos^3 x} \\
&= \dfrac{\sin x}{\cos^3 x} + \dfrac{1}{\sin x \cos x} \\
&= \tan x \sec^2 x + \dfrac{1/(\cos^2 x)}{\sin x \cos x / \cos^2 x}\\
&= \tan x \sec^2 x + \dfrac{\sec^2 x }{\tan x}
\end{align}

step.reason:
\int x^n \, dx = \dfrac{x^{n+1}}{n+1} + C_1 \\
\int \dfrac{1}{x} \, dx = \log |x| + C_2
\\ \text{where } C_1 \text{ and } C_2 \text{ are constants of integration.}
